<emphasis id="B95ED005FFF2FFE8FF3B7F124D13FBFB" bold="true" box="[199,293,1087,1113]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Female.</emphasis>
External morphology similar to male, except as follows: female terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13111092FFF2FFE8FB777F1248DEFBF8" box="[1163,1256,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1922,1946]" captionTargetBox="[166,1431,195,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[156,1432,181,1899]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male and female terminalia of Mayagueza lopesi sp. nov. (40x magnification). a) Epandrial complex, terminal view. b) Hypandrial complex, ventral view. c) Phallus complex, ventral view and ejaculatory apodeme. d) Female terminalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704433/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Fig. 3–d</figureCitation>
)—epiproct and hypoproct with few setae, cercus unequal in width, with microtrichia.
</paragraph>
